body_content.explanation: a national park (= a large area of land protected by the government because of its natural beauty or because it has a special history) in the US state of Florida:
examples: He pointed out the pipeline would be dumping pollution into canals flowing into Biscayne National Park, hardly a solution that protects the environment.
The superintendents of Everglades and Biscayne national parks are interested in establishing a center for scientists and other staffers.
